Dover Street, north side, west from and including Front Street. Note stone pave of the Manhattan Approach to the Brooklyn Bridge. The Franklin Square Station of the Second and Third Aves., Elevated, appears directly under the bridge ramp. The building shown in the far distance, is the Municipal.

About 1923.

P. L. Sperr.

Front Street, east side, north from but not including Dover, to, but not including Roosevelt Streets. (Front Street, is arbitrarily set to run north and south from Coenties Slip, to the Brooklyn Bridge).

April 13, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

ASSUMING STREET TO BE NORTH AND SOUTH.
